  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_12' aria-label=\" S.C. Narang versus State (NCT of Delhi) & Anr. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('12','2025','2025_4_2553_2557','2025INSC688'); ><font size='4'> <strong>S.C. NARANG<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE (NCT OF DELHI) & ANR. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 4 S.C.R. 2553</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 688</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010007112025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : ABHAY S. OKA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, UJJAL BHUYAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose whether the Chairman of Managing Committee which runs the school can be punished for offence of cruelty to the child u/s.75 of the Juvenile Justice (Care and Protection of Children) Act. Headnotes&dagger; Juvenile Justice (Care and Protection of Children) Act, punished for cruelty to a child &ndash; Four year old sexually assaulted by a classmate in the school &ndash; Charge sheet filed against four persons, including appellant-Chairman of Managing Committee &ndash; Special judge issued summons to appellant, attributing negligence to the appellant for<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 22-04-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 2125/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('12','2025','2025_4_2553_2557','2025INSC688','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-